</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eONOlN iAhVxb pf-32_ pf-text-1">According to the World Health Organisation (WHO), worldwide, around 60 million people experience concussions each year.






</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eONOlN iAhVxb pf-34_ pf-text-1">In the UK alone, there are approximately 1.4 million cases of TBI annually, with concussions representing a significant portion of these injuries.







